        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI updated the change - besides docstrings I changed the names of some methods to standardize them across Pylog where it seemed necessary. The old names are still present, but they are now deprecated. They simply call new methods now and in the future all it takes is just remove them so new naming is only used. Same goes with arguments in those old methods.\n\nCertain functions were moved to the utility folder separated between system, styles and other utilities where possible. Those with circular imports were left where they are.\n\nProperties were added for class attributes",
